Definition: a disposition toward schism and secession from a larger group
Example: the principles and practices of separatists; separatism is a serious problem in Quebec; demands for some form of separatism on grounds of religion have been perceived as a threat to mainstream education
Synonyms: noun, person, separatist, disposition, a, toward, schism, and, secession, from, larger, group, the, principles, practices, of, separatists, is, serious, problem, in, Quebec, demands, for, some, form, on, grounds, religion, have, been, perceived, as, threat, to, mainstream, education
Category: noun.attribute
